

works from top to bottom inherits

!important tag -- takes precedence over everything else

:psuedo selectors
    work to get properties of a class
    a:hover -- when you hover over a thing
    
    ul:first-child -- first element
    
vendor prefixes--
    each browser does it own thing to take in a style
    

RESPONSIVE DESIGN - working with multi screen widths

media query - looks for size of screen, tailored to range of output devices w/o changing content
    **e.g. <link rel="stylesheet" media="screen and (max-width: 600px)" href="small.css" />



body{
    background-color: pink;
   }
   
@media screen and (min-width: 300px;){
    body{
        background-color: green;
    }
 }
 
 
@media screen and (min-width: 600px;){
    body{
        background-color: blue;
    }
 }